    int stride_confidence;
    uint64_t hit_count;
    uint64_t miss_count;
    enum { PATTERN_UNKNOWN, PATTERN_SEQUENTIAL, PATTERN_STRIDED, PATTERN_RANDOM } pattern;
    uint32_t prefetch_distance;
} FilePrefetchState;
```

The policy engine computes pattern confidence from stride consistency and dynamically adjusts prefetch_distance using a weighted average of hit/miss ratios. Sequential patterns trigger aggressive read-ahead, while random patterns reduce or disable prefetching to avoid cache pollution. Use per-CPU counters and RCU-protected hash tables to handle concurrent access without locking overhead.

**Test Plan:**
1. **Unit tests**: Validate pattern classification using synthetic traces (sequential bursts, strided arrays, random access)
2. **Integration tests**: Measure cache hit rates under mixed workloads using fio
3. **Stress tests**: Verify correctness under race conditions with concurrent file access
4. **Performance benchmarks**: Compare adaptive prefetching against fixed read-ahead across varied I/O patterns

