**End-to-end flow:** A fault arrives at a global handler, which dispatches to the owning VM's fault context. The handler acquires a per-page lock via CAS to claim the page. If the page is already resident, the fault completes immediately. Otherwise, it enforces the per-VM quota; if quota is exhausted, the request is queued for later processing. If quota is available, I/O is submitted with the configured deadline for read-ahead.

**Per-page state:** Each page maintains: `owner_vm`, `state` (free/claimed/io-pending/resident), `io_refcount`, and `quota_charged` flag.

```c
void handle_fault(page_t *p, vm_t *vm) {
    if (!acquire_page_lock_cas(p)) return;
    if (p->state == RESIDENT) { release_lock(p); return; }
    if (!vm_has_quota(vm)) { enqueue_wait(vm, p); release_lock(p); return; }
    p->state = IO_PENDING;
    p->quota_charged = true;
    release_lock(p);
    submit_io(p, vm, compute_deadline());
}
```

